stylometry:
One of the advantages of a simulation model is that it shows multiple results rather than just one result.  This allows for better comparisons in order to make the best decision.  These results can also be called scenarios, by being able to view multiple scenarios, it helps to narrow it down to the optimal solution.  

Another advantages to a simulation model is that it shows how sensitive the system is to changes in the operating system.  They can answer "what-if" questions that prevent the company from having to actually build a physical model.

Simulation would be a good model to use for a management or business situation because it can save the company money by eliminating the need to build a physical model, this can be done on excel which is virutally free.  It can help management compare results in order to make the best business-like decision for their company.
